What can I say. Even without the main character Maddy, Wolfblood: Season 3 takes storytelling, character development and many other elements (music, dialogue, etc) to the next level. It is definitely one to watch. All 13 episodes + Webisode Series (Jana Bites) will draw you in, desperately wanting to know what will happen. Congrats to the cast and crew

At first I was disappointed because part of the original cast (main character and her family were missing. The first two season developed well wth dynamics of the wolf girl and her family revealing their secrets to their friends. The third season introduction of a shadowy corporation was really a let down. Some of the storylines were less developed than in the two season. What happened to the original writers? I would not recommend this season. .
